annotationA: Translationally controlled tumor protein (Tctp) belongs to the TCTP family. It interacts with the GTPase Rheb to regulate organ growth. Tctp is required for DNA damage response and genome stability
annotationB: 60S ribosomal protein L4; Structural constituent of ribosome. It is involved in the biological process described with: centrosome duplication; translation; Belongs to the universal ribosomal protein uL4 family
